<br>
I agree that warriors are not a solo class.  But I'd wager that none of the classes were &quot;intended&quot; to be solo classes initially. Or the thought was that each would be balanced from a soloing perspective.  <br>
<br>
I think the plan was to have people group. It just turned out that the other classes figured out how to solo (using pets as mini tanks, DoTing, Kiting etc), and the warriors - given our limitations - never could.<br>
<br>
I think that you made a good points regarding damage dealing and taunting.  And in fact, if we were better at damage dealing, we'd probably be a better at soloing.<br>
<br>
If they doubled or tripled our recovery speed - due to warrior fitness/training (or doubled the bandage healing rate) I don't think that it would unbalance the game. <br>
<br>
It wouldn't make much difference in the high end game or in groups because we'd still need the healers and casters. But it sure would let us solo a bit more. <br>
<br>
I don't think that would make things unbalanced in our favor because we're playing catch-up in that area.<br>
